[SN]TITLE[SN]
Eastleigh: Connor Essam and Mikael Mandron join National League club

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
National League Eastleigh have signed defender Connor Essam and striker Mikael Mandron ahead of next season.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Essam, 23, joins from Leyton Orient on a one-year deal, having previously been on loan at Dover last season.
French-born Mandron, 21, has agreed a two-year deal with the Spitfires having been released by Sunderland.
He made seven appearances during a loan spell with Hartlepool last season, scoring in an FA Cup second-round replay win against Salford City.
